    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a loud humming sound but the fan isnt actually spinning. any idea what might be wrong with it and what should i watch out for if i look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A loud humming sound with no fan spin on your AC unit usually points to a motor issue, like a capacitor failure or a seized motor. It's a common problem, but you'll want to be careful when looking at it, especially if you're not familiar with the mechanics. Don't try to fix it if you see any sparking, which is a sign of a serious electrical problem, and always turn off the power at the breaker first. It's best to call a professional HVAC technician to diagnose the exact issue, as these units can be tricky to work on.",
